A 58-year-old man was on Wednesday arrested for allegedly having sexual intercourse with a 20-year-old man in Nnewi North Local Government Area of Anambra State. Police spokesman Haruna Mohammed confirmed the arrest, adding that the suspect said it was intended for money rituals. He said, “On the 8/4/2020 at about 1pm, following a tip-off, police operatives attached to Nnewi Division arrested one Josephat Unachukwu aged 58 years from Edoji Uruagu in Nnewi North LGA of Anambra State. “The suspect allegedly had unlawful carnal knowledge against the order of nature with a 20-year-old man to prepare charms allegedly given to him by a fetish priest for money rituals. The case has been transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department (CID) for discreet investigation on the orders of Commissioner of Police John Abang.